headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham scored 19 points to lead the Detroit Pistons to a 106-92 win over the Brooklyn Nets Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Six Pistons score in double figures to lead Detroit past Nets 106-92

events.name: Atlanta Hawks at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Jalen Johnson scored 29 points and the Atlanta Hawks snapped a four-game skid with a 126-111 victory over the short-handed New Orleans Pelicans on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jalen Johnson's 29 points lead the Hawks past the depleted Pelicans, 126-111

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic had 32 points, nine rebounds and seven assists, Daniel Gafford scored a season-high 18 points, and the Dallas Mavericks beat the Orlando Magic 108-85 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic scores 32 points, Mavericks overwhelm Banchero-less Magic 108-85
